SIMPLE: kinnikinic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kinnikinic
<hw>Kin`ni*ki*nic"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Indian,
literally, a mixture.]</ety> <def>Prepared leaves or bark of certain
plants; -- used by the Indians of the Northwest for smoking, either
mixed with tobacco or as a substitute for it. Also, a plant so used, as
the osier cornel (<spn>Cornus stolonijra</spn>), and the bearberry
(<spn>Arctostaphylus Uva-ursi</spn>).</def> <altsp>[Spelled also
<asp>kinnickinnick</asp> and <asp>killikinick</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kinit</ent>⟦br⟧
